<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

	<PropertyGroup>
		<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>
		<ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
		<Nullable>enable</Nullable>
		<Version>4.9.2-rc.28</Version>
		<PackageReleaseNotes>v4.9.2-rc.28: Pulls in SpawnDev.WebTorrent 3.2.2-rc.2's critical SCTP backpressure multi-awaiter fix. The rc.27 bridge dedup (gating `UnregisterPeer` behind `wasNotified` AND `isLastWireForCanonical`) was correct but uncovered a deeper bug: `RtcPeer.Send`'s rc.1 backpressure logic used `Interlocked.Exchange` on a single `_bufferedAmountLowTcs` slot, so every concurrent `Send()` caller orphaned the previous one. Only the latest awaiter received the OnBufferedAmountLow signal; the rest hung 30s and threw `TimeoutException`. The exception flowed through `Peer.OnConnected` -&gt; `Peer.Destroy(err)` -&gt; `Wire.Destroy()` -&gt; `wire.OnClose`, which the rc.27 bridge correctly identified as a real peer departure and unregistered the peer mid-flight. Manifested in P2P as "No healthy peers available for dispatch" on every 1MB+ buffer transfer (`LargeBuffer_1MB/10MB/100MB`, `DataIntegrity_SHA256`). Diagnosed against `LargeBuffer_1MB_DispatchedOverRealWebRtc_BitExact`: 3 retries, 109s wall time, stack-trace instrumentation pinpointed `RtcPeer.Send` line 336 (`tcs.Task.WaitAsync`). SpawnDev.WebTorrent 3.2.2-rc.2 fixes the race by making `_bufferedAmountLowTcs` a SHARED TCS that all concurrent awaiters reference; `OnBufferedAmountLow` completes the shared TCS to release every awaiter at once, then atomically installs a fresh TCS for the next round. No P2P code changes - the fix lives entirely in the dependency.</PackageReleaseNotes>
		<GeneratePackageOnBuild>True</GeneratePackageOnBuild>
		<GenerateDocumentationFile>true</GenerateDocumentationFile>
		<EmbedAllSources>true</EmbedAllSources>
		<DebugType>Embedded</DebugType>
		<Title>SpawnDev.ILGPU.P2P</Title>
		<Authors>LostBeard</Authors>
		<Description>P2P distributed GPU compute via SpawnDev.WebTorrent. AcceleratorType.P2P — the 7th ILGPU backend. Distributes kernels across connected devices via WebRTC. Scan a QR code, contribute GPU power.</Description>
		<PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/LostBeard/SpawnDev.ILGPU</PackageProjectUrl>
		<PackageLicenseFile>LICENSE.txt</PackageLicenseFile>
		<RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/LostBeard/SpawnDev.ILGPU.git</RepositoryUrl>
		<RepositoryType>git</RepositoryType>
		<PackageTags>P2P;WebRTC;WebTorrent;ILGPU;GPU;DistributedCompute;GPGPU</PackageTags>
		<LangVersion>latest</LangVersion>
		<AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
	</PropertyGroup>

	<ItemGroup>
		<None Include="..\LICENSE.txt" Pack="true" PackagePath="\" />
	</ItemGroup>

	<ItemGroup>
		<ProjectReference Include="..\SpawnDev.ILGPU\SpawnDev.ILGPU.csproj" />
		<PackageReference Include="SpawnDev.WebTorrent" Version="3.2.2-rc.3" />
	</ItemGroup>

</Project>
